<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> gamble on something • take a gamble on something</xh5><p> <i>gamble on something—</i>1. risk money on the unknown result of a race, etc.: Cockfighting is a fight between male chickens (roosters), in which people <u>gamble on</u> the outcome of the fight. 2. act in the hope of smth. being successful, true, etc.: I wouldn’t <u>gamble on</u> the weather being fine. <i>Cf.: you can gamble on that</i>—(coll.) you may be sure of that: There will be trouble for someone. <u>You can gamble on that</u>.</p><p> <i>take a gamble on something</i>— = gamble on something 2: The firm <u>took a gamble on</u> an emerging market with a multi-million dollar investment.</p> </entry>
